## Description

Fixes #18834.

When the parse post-process step unwraps a single-type union (`TSUnionType` with one member) or a parenthesized type (`TSParenthesizedType`), any comments that lived between `=` and the type annotation lose the AST node they were anchored to. They then fall back to the default placement, which can move them in front of the `=`, producing output that no longer matches the source.

### Example (from the issue)

```ts
// Input
type A1 =
  /* 1 */ | /* 2 */ (
    /* 3 */ | /* 4 */ {
        key: string;
      }
  );
```

```ts
// Prettier stable
type A1 /* 2 */ = /* 1 */ /* 3 */ /* 4 */ {
  key: string;
};
```

```ts
// Prettier main (this PR)
type A1 = /* 1 */ /* 2 */ /* 3 */ /* 4 */ {
  key: string;
};
```

### What the fix does

Adds a new comment handler — `handleAssignmentLikeAnnotationLeadingComments` — to the `handleRemainingComment` list. For `VariableDeclarator` / `AssignmentExpression` / `TypeAlias` / `TSTypeAliasDeclaration` enclosing nodes, it attaches `remaining` comments as leading comments on the right-hand side **whenever the comment appears after the `=` token in the source**.

The post-`=` check is important: comments authored *before* the `=` (e.g. `const x /* a */ = …`) are intentional annotations of the left-hand side and must not be moved. Without this guard, existing snapshots in `js/cursor`, `js/explicit-resource-management`, and `js/multiparser-html/language-comment` would change, which we don't want.

### Snapshot churn

Six existing snapshots are updated (TS union, TS intersection, TS intersection consistent-with-flow, TS single-type union, plus the two-variant intersection-parens). In every case the source comment was already after `=`, and the new output preserves that position. Each diff has the same shape:

```diff
- type A6 /*1*/ = C;
+ type A6 = /*1*/ C;
```

This is exactly the bug class the issue reports — these existing snapshots were tests *of* the bug rather than of correct behavior.

A new test fixture covers a focused set of single-type union patterns: `tests/format/typescript/union/single-type/comments.ts`.

