## Summary

Fixes #14625.

The store invalidation detection in `{#each}` blocks only checked for `Identifier` and `MemberExpression` AST node types when looking for store subscriptions. This caused `bind:` on iteration variables to silently fail when the each expression used logical operators or other compound expressions (e.g. `{#each $store.items ?? [] as item}`).

### Root cause

In `EachBlock.js` (transform phase), the `store_to_invalidate` detection at lines 103-114 was:

```js
if (node.expression.type === 'Identifier' || node.expression.type === 'MemberExpression') {
    const id = object(node.expression);
    if (id) {
        const binding = context.state.scope.get(id.name);
        if (binding?.kind === 'store_sub') {
            store_to_invalidate = id.name;
        }
    }
}
```

When the expression is `$form.priceRules ?? []`, the AST type is `LogicalExpression`, which fails the type check.

### Fix

Use `node.metadata.expression.dependencies` to find `store_sub` bindings instead of checking AST node types. This is the same approach already used for the `uses_store` flag (lines 60-65) and works regardless of the expression's AST shape.

