previously, 
```ts
function foo() {
    query: while (true) {
        continue query;
        break query
    }
}
```

would generate

```ts
function foo() {
    __vite_ssr_import_0__.query: while (true) {
        continue __vite_ssr_import_0__.query;
        break __vite_ssr_import_0__.query
    }
}
```

This is invalid, as the spec says:
```
continue [no LineTerminator here] LabelIdentifier[?Yield, ?Await] ;
```

`LabelIdentifier` is an `Identifier`, member expressions are not allowed.


It now generates

```ts
function foo() {
    query: while (true) {
        continue query;
        break query
    }
}
```

Static Vapor DOM events are compiled to document-level delegated handlers by default. If an ancestor listener stops propagation, for example a common parent `@click.stop`, the event never reaches `document` and the delegated child handler is skipped.

Add a Vapor-only compiler option, `eventDelegation`, so libraries that need native propagation compatibility can opt out of delegated event codegen. When disabled, eligible static DOM events are compiled to direct element listeners while keeping the default delegated behavior unchanged.

### usage
```js
// @vitejs/plugin-vue
vue({
  template: {
    compilerOptions: {
      eventDelegation: false,
    },
  },
})
```

Solid documents the same caveat here:
[docs.solidjs.com/concepts/components/event-handlers#event-delegation-considerations](https://docs.solidjs.com/concepts/components/event-handlers#event-delegation-considerations)


